Just learned how to do some git commands

git init --> creates a new empty repository
git commit --m to send a message on your commit
git add --> if I add just a "." it will add all the new files present in the directory
    |--> If I want to add some specific files I have to do "add XXXX.extension"
git restore --staged
git status --> shows if sth is waiting to be committed or not
git branch --> creates a branch in my repository
git merge --> merges my branch to the main branch
git branch -d [branch-name]
   |--> deletes a branch

gh pr create --title "Your PR title" --body "Description of changes"
  |--> this is the structure of a PR message 

